article.headline: UMKC 84, Utah Valley State 77
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Carlton Aaron scored 26 points and grabbed 13 rebounds as Missouri-Kansas City beat Utah Valley State 84-77 Monday night. The Kangaroos (12-8) never trailed in the game, but the Wolverines (11-11) made it close in the second half, closing to within four points in the last minute. Quinton Day, who finished with 20 points, was 8-of-8 from the free-throw line in the last 58 seconds to help the Kangaroos escape with the win. UMKC took a 16-4 lead in the first 5:21 of the game but was never able to shake Utah Valley State. The Kangaroos led 45-31 at halftime, but shot just 39 percent (12-of-31) from the field in the second half to the Wolverines' 47 percent (18-of-38). Ronnie Price kept Utah Valley State close with a season-high 35 points. David Heck added 16 points, including three 3-pointers in the last four minutes, and 11 rebounds. Aaron shot 10-of-14 from the floor, and his double-double was his seventh of the season. Mike English added 20 points for the Kangaroos, and Tim Blackwell had 10. UMKC shot 25-of-28 from the free throw-line, including Day's 9-of-9. The Wolverines made 5-of-8 (63 percent) free throws.
